                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">504.418A2/270: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Diekema</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-10T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 10, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. [For Miller.] Your 60, Conference No. 28. You are authorized to sign any
                    formal and official record of the proceedings <pb facs="0301" n="221"
                        xml:id="pg_221"/> which you deem in proper form and you are the judges of
                    what is proper form, provided it is merely a record and binds nobody to
                    anything.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
